-- UBA of Nigeria Plans to Acquire Banks in Africa, Punch Reports
-- B y   V i n c e n t   N w a n m a
-- 2012-02-21T09:11:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-21/uba-of-nigeria-plans-to-acquire-banks-in-africa-punch-reports.html
United Bank for Africa Plc , a
Nigerian lender, plans to acquire lenders in different regions
on the continent, Punch  reported , citing Managing Director
Phillips Oduoza.  The bank will raise equity for the investments once
conditions in the Nigerian market improve, the Lagos-based
newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Vincent Nwanma in Lagos at 
 vnwanma@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dulue Mbachu at 
 dmbachu@bloomberg.net  